#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.71"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.71:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: anāgatabhayavaggo (bj)
msgctxt "an5.71:0.2"
msgid "8. Yodhājīvavagga"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.71:0.3"
msgid "71. Paṭhamacetovimuttiphalasutta"
msgstr ""

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.84"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.71:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Pañcime, bhikkhave, dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā cetovimuttiphalā ca honti "
"cetovimuttiphalānisaṃsā ca, paññāvimuttiphalā ca honti "
"paññāvimuttiphalānisaṃsā ca."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.71:2.1"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr ""

#. VAR: paṭikūlasaññī → paṭikkūlasaññī (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.71:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu asubhānupassī kāye viharati, āhāre paṭikūlasaññī, "
"sabbaloke anabhiratasaññī, sabbasaṅkhāresu aniccānupassī, maraṇasaññā kho "
"panassa ajjhattaṃ sūpaṭṭhitā hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.71:2.3"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā cetovimuttiphalā ca "
"honti cetovimuttiphalānisaṃsā ca, paññāvimuttiphalā ca honti "
"paññāvimuttiphalānisaṃsā ca."
msgstr ""

#. VAR: paññāvimutto ca hoti → paññāvimutto ca (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.71:2.4"
msgid "Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cetovimutto ca hoti paññāvimutto ca hoti—"
msgstr ""

# These similes all relate meaningfully to their explanations, but it’s not always possible to capture this in English. 1. “lifted the crossbar” = overcome ignorance, removed the blocks to knowledge. 2. “filled in the trench” = ended samsara. This one is obscure, but I think it means that you’re trapped by trenches, kept within the bounds of samsara, and when they’re filled in you can escape. 3. “pulled up the pillar” = give up craving. This one relies on a pun in the Pali: pillar = esika, which also means “seeking”. No pillar, no seeking, no craving. 4. Unbarred = giving up fiver lower fetters, a fetter is a bar. “lowering the flag” = giving up conceit. The flag is used as an identifier so you know who is who: no flag, no self.
#. VAR: saṃkiṇṇaparikho → saṃkiṇṇaparikkho (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an5.71:2.5"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ‘bhikkhu ukkhittapaligho itipi, saṃkiṇṇaparikho "
"itipi, abbūḷhesiko itipi, niraggaḷo itipi, ariyo pannaddhajo pannabhāro "
"visaṃyutto itipi’."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.71:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ukkhittapaligho hoti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.71:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno avijjā pahīnā hoti ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā "
"anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.71:3.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ukkhittapaligho hoti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an5.71:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saṃkiṇṇaparikho hoti?"
msgstr ""

#. VAR: ponobhaviko → ponobbhaviko (s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an5.71:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno ponobhaviko jātisaṃsāro pahīno hoti ucchinnamūlo "
"tālāvatthukato anabhāvaṃkato āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.71:4.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saṃkiṇṇaparikho hoti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.85"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an5.71:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu abbūḷhesiko hoti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.71:5.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno taṇhā pahīnā hoti ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā "
"anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.71:5.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu abbūḷhesiko hoti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an5.71:6.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu niraggaḷo hoti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.71:6.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno pañcorambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni pahīnāni honti "
"ucchinnamūlāni tālāvatthukatāni anabhāvaṅkatāni āyatiṃ anuppādadhammāni."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.71:6.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu niraggaḷo hoti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an5.71:7.1"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ariyo pannaddhajo pannabhāro visaṃyutto hoti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.71:7.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno asmimāno pahīno hoti ucchinnamūlo tālāvatthukato "
"anabhāvaṅkato āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.71:7.3"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ariyo pannaddhajo pannabhāro visaṃyutto hotī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.71:7.4"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
